title.narrative: The Feed the Future Innovation Lab for Small-scale Irrigation

description.narrative: The Feed the Future Innovation Lab for Small-Scale Irrigation, a project of the U.S. Governments Feed the Future Initiative, is a five-year project in Ethiopia, Ghana and Tanzania aimed at benefiting the regions farmers by improving effective use of scarce water supplies through interventions in small-scale irrigation. The project, led by the Norman Borlaug Institute for International Agriculture at Texas A&M University and funded by the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID,) intends to develop management protocols and practices to reduce poverty and improve nutrition.
